										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Cashea Raises $100M To Strengthen Venezuela&#8217;s Consumer Economy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Venezuelan fintech Cashea announces $100M for interest-free consumer finance The Venezuelan fintech firm, which provides interest-free consumer credit, has closed $100 million in institutional funding from both global and Latin American investors. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing round, consisting of a previously unreported $40 million Series A which closed in March 2026 and a $60 million Series B which closed in June 2026, was announced Tuesday. Spice Expeditions led the Series A with $20 million in equity and $20 million in debt from Architect Capital. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">FinSight Ventures led the Series B with contributions from Spice Expeditions, Endeavor Catalyst, US endowments, and international and Latin American investors. The round is one of the largest ever secured by a Venezuelan fintech and signals investor optimism about the region’s recovering economy.</span></p>
<h2><b>Cashea Expands Access To Interest-Free Financing</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Created by Pedro Vallenilla in 2022, Cashea was established to restart access to consumer lending, which had contracted significantly during Venezuela&#8217;s long years of economic crisis. The service enables shoppers to buy items online or in person with 0% interest installment plans. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Customers make one down payment through the Cashea app and then pay the remaining balance in bi-weekly equal installments. Now, Cashea reaches over 10 million consumer accounts &#8211; more than half of the country&#8217;s adult population.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its platform is integrated with some 40,000 retailers across Venezuela, processing more than 100 million transactions to date. This injection reflects growing international conviction in the country’s private sector, as well as Venezuelan consumers’ trust in our ability to serve them.</span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports New Financial Products And Merchant Growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203684" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203684" class="size-full wp-image-203684" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-glowing-_fU-o6-ShXhKxWUN8g8Zrxg_hcp2_cqrS-e_nQsrfZTzmA.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing digital financial services supporting consumers and merchants." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203684" class="wp-caption-text">Cashea expands financial access with digital credit and payment solutions supporting consumers and businesses. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cashea plans to invest the full $100 million within Venezuela to expand access to credit and introduce additional financial services beyond its core buy now, pay later offering. The company aims to develop new payment, savings, and commerce solutions for consumers while providing merchants with additional tools to support business growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The announcement follows a recent earthquake in Venezuela, during which Cashea temporarily waived late payment fees, advanced cash to merchants to improve liquidity, and expanded credit access to help affected families replace essential goods.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/gritt-raises-26m-ai-construction-robotics/" data-wpel-link="internal">Gritt Raises $26M to Expand AI-Powered Construction Robotics</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Venezuela&#8217;s Fintech Recovery</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest funding attracted an unusually diverse investor base, including venture capital firms, university endowments, institutional investors, and regional funds. Many investors travelled to Venezuela to observe Cashea&#8217;s operations and meet </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/merchant" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">merchants</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> using the platform before committing capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cashea says its long-term strategy extends beyond instalment payments. The company intends to build a broader financial ecosystem that enables Venezuelans to pay, save, and access financial services while helping businesses manage transactions more efficiently.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As consumer confidence gradually improves, Cashea is positioning itself as a key financial infrastructure provider supporting everyday commerce across the country. With millions of active users already relying on its platform, the company believes expanding digital credit will play an important role in strengthening Venezuela&#8217;s retail economy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cashea-raises-100m-expand-consumer-credit-venezuela/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cashea Raises $100M to Expand Interest-Free Consumer Credit in Venezuela</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
