					<description><![CDATA[<p>Gritt Raises $26M To Scale AI Construction Systems Gritt raised $26 million, led by Obvious Ventures, to expand AI-powered infrastructure automation. Union Square Ventures and Active Impact Investments also participated,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/gritt-raises-26m-ai-construction-robotics/" data-wpel-link="internal">Gritt Raises $26M to Expand AI-Powered Construction Robotics</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Gritt Raises $26M To Scale AI Construction Systems</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gritt raised $26 million, led by Obvious Ventures, to expand AI-powered infrastructure automation. Union Square Ventures and Active Impact Investments also participated, alongside existing investors First Round Capital, Climactic, Congruent Ventures, and VSC Ventures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest investment brings Gritt&#8217;s total funding to $32.4 million. The company plans to use the capital to expand operations and further develop its intelligent robotics platform designed for complex outdoor construction environments.</span></p>
<h2><b>Robotics Platform Tackles Construction Labour Shortages</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by Puneet Puri and Vishal Dugar, Gritt develops robotic systems for construction equipment automation. Its AI-powered system autonomously performs material handling, assembly, placement, verification, and project planning tasks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Instead of doing away with equipment currently utilized on site, Gritt&#8217;s tech will integrate with existing hardware, which would enable contractors to utilize automation on the machines they currently own, and help ensure robots and their human counterparts can work side by side safely. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer Puneet Puri explained how building automation into construction jobs out of doors is more challenging due to shifting weather patterns and terrain, as well as other unforeseen issues. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“We’ve designed our Physical AI for exactly that, allowing construction projects like solar, bridge and road projects, along with those on large infrastructure builds like data centres, to run faster with robotic support,” Puri said.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Improves Productivity Across Infrastructure Projects<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203680" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203680" class="size-full wp-image-203680" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcasing-a-sprawli_yb8-mHRMV7qqeVIbjY_mMw_YoPwH2IERSaAF2EN3QZzPA.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI construction robots installing solar panels with real-time data monitoring." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203680" class="wp-caption-text">Gritt’s AI platform enhances construction efficiency with autonomous robotics and real-time site intelligence. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company says its platform continuously improves by learning from every deployment. Tasks that previously required months of system training can now be adapted within days, allowing robots to perform highly </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/precise" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">precise</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> work across different construction projects.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond automation, Gritt captures real-time operational data from construction sites, including completed work, material movement, and changing site conditions. This information helps project supervisors make faster operational decisions and improve scheduling efficiency.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has already deployed its systems with several major U.S. construction firms building utility-scale solar installations. According to Gritt, its robots have autonomously placed tens of thousands of solar panels without a single reported breakage.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industry challenges continue to create demand for automation. With more than 40% of the U.S. construction workforce expected to retire by 2031 and productivity declining across the sector, companies are increasingly turning to AI and robotics to address labour shortages and improve project delivery.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/sila-raises-300m-expand-us-battery-production/" data-wpel-link="internal">Sila Raises $300M to Expand U.S. Battery Material Production</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Investors See Opportunity In Physical AI</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Obvious Ventures said Gritt is creating a new category of physical AI by bringing intelligent automation to some of the most demanding industrial environments. Investors believe the company&#8217;s ability to learn from each deployment creates a long-term competitive advantage.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gritt’s roadmap is to transform the AI into a more comprehensive site intelligence platform that tracks resource utilization, identifies potential workflow roadblocks, and assists project managers making real-time choices. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The startup ultimately envisions its technology reducing hard manual labor for construction workers and allowing contractors to speed up enormous infrastructure projects. Gritt believes intelligent robotics will become an increasingly important part of modern construction.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/gritt-raises-26m-ai-construction-robotics/" data-wpel-link="internal">Gritt Raises $26M to Expand AI-Powered Construction Robotics</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
