					<description><![CDATA[<p>Sila Raises $300M To Scale U.S. Battery Manufacturing Sila has raised $300 million in a private equity fundraising round to bolster its on-shoring of its silicon-carbon anode production technology. These</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/sila-raises-300m-expand-us-battery-production/" data-wpel-link="internal">Sila Raises $300M to Expand U.S. Battery Material Production</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Sila Raises $300M To Scale U.S. Battery Manufacturing</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sila has raised $300 million in a private equity fundraising round to bolster its on-shoring of its silicon-carbon </span><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/materials-science/anode" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">anode</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> production technology. These new funds will be utilized to further expand Sila’s production capacity with Phase 2 of its Moses Lake plant on the horizon.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In the new funding round led by Atreides Management and Sutter Hill Ventures, there was participation from existing investors 8VC, Bessemer Venture Partners, Matrix Partners, funds and accounts managed by T. Rowe Price Associates, Inc., and new investors. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Silicon-carbon anode provider, its vision for the American battery supply chain to facilitate increased demand for electric vehicles, AI, robotics, satellites, drones and other next generation technologies.</span></p>
<h2><b>Titan Silicon Technology Targets Next-Generation Batteries</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sila, which was established in 2011, has created silicon carbon (Si/C) anode materials to replace the graphite in batteries for electric vehicles. The company’s Titan Silicon technology increases energy density by between 20 and 40 percent, leading to batteries which are smaller, lighter, and charge more quickly. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“The new investment will enable Sila to ramp up production to serve our growing customer demand and invest further in US based battery innovations,” Chief Executive Officer Gene Berdichevsky, a co-founder of Sila, stated in the announcement. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Reducing reliance on foreign supply of battery materials is critical, and Sila is enabling the US to strengthen our role as the world&#8217;s leading innovators. China continues to dominate global anode processing and battery cell manufacturing, driving strategic supply chain concerns. </span></p>
<h2><b>Moses Lake Expansion Supports Long-Term Growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203672" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203672" class="size-full wp-image-203672" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-vibrant-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-_f3ao0gmnUoCelAFHVZltsw_1lVtcVrlTAqrQ39uGcCj4w.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing large-scale battery manufacturing and advanced energy production systems." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203672" class="wp-caption-text">Sila scales battery manufacturing to support next-generation energy demand and domestic production growth. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sila completed construction of its first manufacturing facility in Moses Lake during 2025 and has already begun production. The initial Phase 1 operation is capable of producing approximately 2 GWh of silicon-carbon anode material annually.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company plans to expand the site significantly over the coming years. Once fully developed, the facility could reach 250 GWh of production capacity, making it one of the world&#8217;s largest anode manufacturing plants.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The expansion is also expected to create hundreds of skilled manufacturing jobs while supporting local economic growth in Washington State.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sutter Hill Ventures said Sila has successfully transformed laboratory innovation into large-scale industrial production, demonstrating that advanced battery manufacturing can be built and scaled within the United States.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/natural-raises-30m-agentic-payments-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Natural Raises $30M to Build Payments Infrastructure for AI Agents</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Domestic Battery Supply Chain Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding reflects growing investor confidence in battery technologies that improve both performance and supply chain resilience. Beyond electric vehicles, Sila&#8217;s materials are increasingly considered for artificial intelligence infrastructure and aerospace applications worldwide. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They also support consumer electronics, defence systems, and advanced energy storage across multiple high-growth industries globally. The company said the investment will accelerate Titan Silicon production and support future manufacturing expansion plans. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It expects growing customer demand to drive continued investment in advanced battery manufacturing capabilities across facilities. Global competition around battery technology and critical minerals continues intensifying as strategic supply chains rapidly evolve worldwide. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sila is positioning itself as a key domestic supplier reducing reliance on foreign battery supply chains. By combining proprietary American technology with large-scale manufacturing, the company strengthens the country&#8217;s long-term battery ecosystem. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/sila-raises-300m-expand-us-battery-production/" data-wpel-link="internal">Sila Raises $300M to Expand U.S. Battery Material Production</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
