<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Day trading often means borrowing money (leverage) from your broker or the exchange. This lets you take bigger positions than your balance would usually allow, which can really boost your gains. The downside is that losses get bigger too. Managing your margin isn’t optional. It’s survival.</span></p>
